<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-253-394  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 253 394.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 12 1989 n1175* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cognos takes Systematica, Bournemouth's Virtual Software Factory.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cognos Inc. (contracts)Systematica Ltd. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    COGNF.andO;Product:   Virtual Software Factory (Program development software)(marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing AgreementsComputer-Aided Software EngineeringSoftware PublishersProgram Development ToolsMarketing StrategySoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COGNOS TAKES SYSTEMATICA, BOURNEMOUTH'S VIRTUAL SOFTWAREandM;FACTORYandM;Cognos Inc, the Canadian software house based in Ottawa, Ontario,andM;and developer of the PowerHouse fourth generation language has signed upBournmouth, Hampshire-based Systematica Ltd as its computer-aided softwareengineering partner in a technology and marketing agreement signed this week.andO;Cognos is to take Systematica's Virtual Software Factory product, aknowledge-based software development design tool that uses object-orientedtechniques to improve programmer productivity and system quality: code can begenerated from the VSF design model once it is complete and consistent, andsubsequent changes to the code are reflected in the design model.andP;  Theproduct runs on VAX/VMS and Sun workstations, and Systematica has atechnology agreement with DEC to develop VSF-based software tools addressingthe various European design standards.andP;  An IBM PS/2 version is also underdevelopment.andP;  Cognos will launch its own version of VSF by the end of 1989,and will eventually fully integrate it with PowerHouse, now installed at12,000 minicomputer sites worldwide, mostly on DEC and Hewlett-Packardhardware.andP;  Cognos says the move is part of its general strategy to expand thePowerHouse environment to cover all aspects of software development - itrecently added StarBase, an SQL compliant relati onal database (CI No 1,084),and now runs on Hewlett-Packard minis under the HP/UX Unix implementati on.andO;Versions for Data General's new AViiON family and for the IBM AS/400 areplanned (CI No 1,173).andO;</TEXT></DOC>